ke Thacher, and Robert Pierpont Blake."},{"number":2,"category":"family","header":"Three children dead before age three, 1869-1883","body":"Charles and Harriet Blake lost three of their seven children to early death across fourteen years: firstborn Jane in 1869 at eight days, Walter Whitney in 1879 at age two, and Henrietta MacWhorter in 1883 at eighteen months. Their four surviving children — Anson Stiles, Eliza Seely, Edwin Tyler, and Robert Pierpont — all reached adulthood."}],"slug":"charles-blake-1826"},"HD4108":{"id":"HD4108","former_ids":[],"is_placeholder":false,"has_descendants_documented":false,"bio":{"first_name":"Jane","last_name":"Blake","married_names":[],"gender":"female","display_name":"Jane Blake"},"birth":{"year":1869,"month":8,"day":10,"city":"San Francisco","county":"San Francisco County","state":"California","country":"United States"},"baptism":{},"death":{"year":1869,"month":8,"day":18,"city":"San Francisco","county":"San Francisco County","state":"California","country":"United States"},"residence":{},"burial":{},"classification":{"is_thomas_descendant":true,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_thomas_spouse":false,"is_talcott_spouse":false,"generation_from_thomas":9,"include_in_path_calculation":true,"descent_paths_to_thomas":1,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":true,"is_progenitor":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"parents":{"father_id":"HD1567","father_name":"Charles Thompson Blake","mother_id":"X01504","mother_name":"Harriet Waters Stiles Blake"},"marriages":[],"education":[],"career":[],"military_service":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"artworks":[],"tags":["died_in_infancy","died_young"],"research_tags":[],"cross_connections":[],"narrative_blocks":[{"number":1,"category":"death","header":"Born and dead within eight days, August 1869","body":"Jane Blake, firstborn of Charles Thompson Blake and Harriet Waters Stiles, was born in San Francisco on August 10, 1869 and died eight days later on August 18. She was the first of three Blake children to die young; her surviving four siblings were born across the next seventeen years."}],"quotes":[],"sources":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"slug":"jane-blake-1869"},"HD4106":{"id":"HD4106","former_ids":[],"is_placeholder":false,"has_descendants_documented":false,"bio":{"first_name":"Anson","middle_name":"Stiles","last_name":"Blake","married_names":[],"gender":"male","display_name":"Anson Stiles Blake","photo_url":"https://res.cloudinary.com/dc5clrqtw/image/upload/v1778626145/ansonstilesblake_lel0iw.jpg"},"birth":{"year":1870,"month":8,"day":6,"city":"San Francisco","county":"San Francisco County","state":"California","country":"United States"},"baptism":{},"death":{"year":1959,"month":8,"day":17,"city":"Berkeley","county":"Alameda County","state":"California","country":"United States"},"residence":{},"burial":{"cemetery_id":"CEM310"},"classification":{"is_thomas_descendant":true,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_thomas_spouse":false,"is_talcott_spouse":false,"generation_from_thomas":9,"include_in_path_calculation":true,"descent_paths_to_thomas":1,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":true,"is_progenitor":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"notable":{"is_notable":true,"notable_category":["civic_leader","businessman"],"notable_blurb":"Grand old man of Stiles Hall, UC Berkeley","primary_url":"https://www.findagrave.com/memorial/137272119/anson_stiles-blake","primary_url_label":"FindAGrave: Anson Stiles Blake"},"parents":{"father_id":"HD1567","father_name":"Charles Thompson Blake","mother_id":"X01504","mother_name":"Harriet Waters Stiles Blake"},"number_of_marriages":1,"marriages":[{"marriage_number":1,"spouse_id":"I00593","date_year":1894,"location_state":"California","location_country":"United States","end_type":"death","end_year":1959,"children_ids":[]}],"education":[{"institution":"University of California, Berkeley","degree":"A.B.; honorary LL.D.","notes":"One of UC Berkeley's oldest living graduates at his death in 1959. Awarded honorary Doctor of Laws by the university."}],"career":[{"role":"President","organization":"Blake Brothers Co. (Richmond, California — quarry firm)"},{"role":"Chairman of the Board","organization":"University YMCA at UC Berkeley (Stiles Hall)","notes":"Served as chairman for fifty years; declared 'Grand old man of Stiles Hall' by California State Legislature resolution."},{"role":"President","organization":"California Historical Society","start_year":1922,"notes":"Reactivated the Society in 1922 after it had lapsed; made honorary member for life."},{"role":"Active Board Member","organization":"Save the Redwoods League / California Academy of Sciences / Friends of the Bancroft Library"}],"military_service":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[{"landmark_id":"LM123"}],"naming_inspiration":[],"artworks":[],"tags":[],"research_tags":[],"cross_connections":[{"type":"parallel_careers","related_id":"HD6074","display_label":"also a pioneering historian of Gold Rush California"}],"narrative_blocks":[{"number":1,"category":"civic","header":"Grand old man of Stiles Hall, fifty years","body":"Anson Stiles Blake chaired the board of the University YMCA at UC Berkeley for fifty years — the building, Stiles Hall, took its name from a benefactor in his Stiles family line. The California State Legislature formally named him the 'Grand old man of Stiles Hall' in recognition of that service."},{"number":2,"category":"civic","header":"Reactivated the California Historical Society, 1922","body":"When the California Historical Society had lapsed, Anson Stiles Blake organized its 1922 revival and served as president. The Society later made him an honorary member for life. He sat on the boards of the Save the Redwoods League, California Academy of Sciences, and Friends of the Bancroft Library."},{"number":3,"category":"career","header":"Family quarry firm at Richmond, California","body":"Anson presided over Blake Brothers Co., the family quarry business at Richmond, California — extending into industrial materials a Blake-family talent for working stone that had begun with his grandfather Eli Whitney Blake's invention of the stone crusher in the 1850s."}],"quotes":[],"sources":[{"label":"FindAGrave memorial 137272119","url":"https://www.findagrave.com/memorial/137272119/anson_stiles-blake"}],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"slug":"anson-blake-1870"},"HD4099":{"id":"HD4099","former_ids":[],"is_placeholder":false,"has_descendants_documented":false,"bio":{"first_name":"Eliza","middle_name":"Seely","last_name":"Thacher","maiden_name":"Blake","married_names":[],"gender":"female","display_name":"Eliza Seely Blake Thacher","photo_url":"https://res.cloudinary.com/dc5clrqtw/image/upload/v1778625538/elizathacher_mvu2mt.png"},"birth":{"year":1872,"month":8,"day":3,"city":"San Francisco","county":"San Francisco County","state":"California","country":"United States"},"baptism":{},"death":{"year":1944,"month":10,"day":19,"city":"Ojai","county":"Ventura County","state":"California","country":"United States"},"residence":{},"burial":{"cemetery_id":"CEM009","plot_notes":"Memorial shared with husband Sherman Day Thacher."},"classification":{"is_thomas_descendant":true,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_thomas_spouse":false,"is_talcott_spouse":false,"generation_from_thomas":9,"include_in_path_calculation":true,"descent_paths_to_thomas":1,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":true,"is_progenitor":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"parents":{"father_id":"HD1567","father_name":"Charles Thompson Blake","mother_id":"X01504","mother_name":"Harriet Waters Stiles Blake"},"number_of_marriages":1,"marriages":[{"marriage_number":1,"spouse_id":"I00592","date_year":1896,"date_month":6,"date_day":24,"location_city":"Berkeley","location_county":"Alameda County","location_state":"California","location_country":"United States","children_ids":["HD4100","HD4115","HD4116","HD4117","HD4101","HD4102","HD4103","HD4104","